            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">Home for Jewish Widows and Orphans</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Corner Jackson and Chippewa Streets—4th
                    District</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">____________________</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)"><placeName>NEW ORLEANS</placeName>, <date><emph rend="italics"
                        >January</emph> 1865—5625</date></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">As the Committee appointed to make arrangements for celebrating<lb/>
                the Tenth Anniversary of the above Institution, the undersigned beg to<lb/> remind
                YOU and its many kind patrons of the same, assuring you no<lb/> efforts will be
                spared to make it equally interesting as on previous<lb/> occasions. We have secured
                the Masonic Hall, on <placeName>St. Charles street</placeName>, and<lb/> again
                decided on that historical day, <date>Sunday, the 8th</date> inst., at 11 A.
                M.,<lb/> when we trust our efforts in that sacred cause for which we labor, and<lb/>
                the same interest and liberality will be displayed as in previous years, by<lb/>
                which the Hearts of those deriving the Benefits of our Holy Charity<lb/> may be
                cheered by the presence of a large audience.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The arrangements made are; The <persName>Rev. H Edinger</persName>
                will open<lb/> the Ceremonies by an appropriate Prayer. <persName>Mr. David
                    Goldman</persName>, (a young native of our city,) will deliver the Oration. The
                Orphans, under the<lb/> tuition of <persName>Miss Julia Hart</persName>, will give
                various recitations.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Messrs. Oliviera</persName> and
                    <persName>Grueling</persName>, have kindly volunteered their<lb/> valuable
                musical abilities; with other intellectual amusements.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Come one! Come all! To the aid of one of the noblest
                Institutions<lb/> of our People.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Remember—“He who gives to the Poor lendeth to the Lord!”</p>
